The important clue is here:

cannot read admin account info, error: account not found 6788bafb4b40bd002623d3a0

and

StatefulSet noobaa-db-pg
creationTimestamp: 2026-06-18T07:42:06Z

while

NooBaa CR creationTimestamp: 2025-01-16

This strongly suggests that the NooBaa PostgreSQL database was recreated/recovered on June 18, but the NooBaa CR and secrets are from January 2025.

As a result:

NooBaa operator secret exists.

noobaa-admin secret exists.

NooBaa core is running.

The account ID stored in the auth token (6788bafb4b40bd002623d3a0) no longer exists in the recreated database.


This is why every RPC call fails with:

UNAUTHORIZED Message=account not found 6788bafb4b40bd002623d3a0


---

Verify whether DB was recreated

Run:

oc get events -n openshift-storage --sort-by=.lastTimestamp | grep -i noobaa-db

and

oc get pvc db-noobaa-db-pg-0 -o yaml -n openshift-storage | egrep "creationTimestamp|uid"

I expect the DB PVC or StatefulSet was recreated around June 18.


---

Next check

Let's see whether the NooBaa database still contains the admin account.

Execute:

oc rsh noobaa-db-pg-0

Inside the pod:

psql -U postgres nbcore

Then:

select _id,email from accounts;

and

select count(*) from accounts;

Paste the output.


---

If accounts table is empty

Then the NooBaa metadata DB has been reinitialized.

In that case the fastest recovery is usually:

1. Backup current NooBaa CR.


2. Remove NooBaa resources.


3. Let ODF recreate NooBaa.


4. Verify BackingStore/BucketClass become Ready.




---

Before doing anything destructive

Check whether ODF object storage is actually being used:

oc get obc -A
oc get objectbucketclaim -A
oc get objectbucket -A
oc get cephobjectstoreuser -n openshift-storage

You already showed:

oc get obc -A
No resources found

which is a good sign, but let's also verify the Ceph object store users.

Run:

oc get cephobjectstoreuser -n openshift-storage

and

oc get cephobjectstore -n openshift-storage

If only the default NooBaa user exists and there are no OBCs, then rebuilding NooBaa becomes much lower risk.

At this point I do not think this is a Ceph issue. Ceph is secondary here. The failure is inside the NooBaa metadata/auth database, likely after the noobaa-db-pg recreation on June 18.
